I understand that people are still in shock, devastated, and currently in survival mode. But as I sat on the shore while my daughter surfed, I got the first glimpse of hope. I was reminded that you can find joy doing the things you love and through the happiness of these little humans. Our children have survived a pandemic and now faced a tragedy. Their mental health may seem intact at the moment, but what’s the bigger picture look like. I would like to use this space to ask for donation of boards that will benefit the local kids displaced by the fires and lost everything. (Venmo funds will not be used towards this as I believe we as a community can rally what we already have.) Get them back into the water, doing what they love. If you have a surfboard, bodyboard or skateboard that is collecting dust (I have a few in my garage), let’s get someone on it! If you have a child or know of one in need, please tag them below. Share this post, tag a pro surfer! Leave details of what you ride and together let’s make the connection by reinstating the joy that this catastrophic disaster has tried to destroy. 
photo: @lahainalifestyle

12 years ago, with an iPhone and a semi-waterproof case (that occasionally leaked), and a makeshift fisheye lens that I superglued to the case. Not even sure what iPhone it was, maybe 3? When I fell in love with photography. Didn’t even own a GoPro or camera yet. When it was a passion before a career. It’s been a while since I’ve used my camera stuff, but recently been itching to dust it off! Hit me up if you’re on Maui and need photos for something! @2scoopsofaloha remember these days?! #shoreymadness

“Another one” – in DJ Khaled’s voice
 
Payton has blown our minds, landing a spot on a National Elite team roster. Her hard work speaks volumes and we’re just trying our best to make it all happen for her. Alone, we can’t, but I’m not giving up just yet. With little time to prepare, we are attempting to tackle Miami in January, a San Diego training camp in June and potentially playing at the Donosti Cup in Spain a month later. I’m nauseous just thinking about it all, but damn she deserves a shot, and this is it.
***If you would like to support our girl, please comment the days below and send venmo to @kauisouza .
